for both our businesses,

23:36.311 --> 23:39.072
"and, so, look forward
to your response.

23:39.107 --> 23:40.488
"Yours, Jerry Cutler."

23:40.522 --> 23:41.489
[EXHALES]

23:42.455 --> 23:44.871
You want me to
pay this guy a visit?

23:44.906 --> 23:47.080
Kick his ass
and make him cry?

23:49.117 --> 23:51.084
Hmm?

23:51.119 --> 23:53.604
These Green Acres guys
breathing down our backs?

23:53.639 --> 23:54.640
What can I do?

24:01.405 --> 24:02.751
[SPOON CLATTERS]

24:05.478 --> 24:06.652
You can clear my tray.

24:09.689 --> 24:12.381
I'll get Ms Oatlash. I'm done now. You can do it.

24:15.108 --> 24:16.247
[QUINCANNON SNIFFS
AND CLEARS THROAT]

24:26.326 --> 24:27.327
[KEYBOARD KEYS CLACKING]

24:30.538 --> 24:32.263
Never mind, Donnie.
Thank you.

24:38.546 --> 24:40.858
A right-hand man
with no right hand.

24:53.043 --> 24:54.769
[FLAMES CRACKLING]

25:20.519 --> 25:25.109
♪ I'm livin'
in the lonely zone

25:25.144 --> 25:29.700
♪ I've been here
since you've been gone

25:29.735 --> 25:34.498
♪ It's so strange
and all alone

25:34.533 --> 25:36.811
♪ Livin' in the lonely zone

25:38.916 --> 25:41.505
♪ In the heart of the city[CAR HORN HONKING]

25:41.540 --> 25:42.541
[HONKING]

25:43.645 --> 25:46.303
♪ With people all around

25:46.337 --> 25:47.338
[TULIP REVS ENGINE]

25:47.994 --> 25:49.237
♪ I'm alone...

25:52.378 --> 25:53.586
TULIP: Howdy, partner.

25:55.174 --> 25:56.416
Miss me?

26:01.767 --> 26:03.009
One of those.

26:09.257 --> 26:10.258
[EXHALES]

26:11.673 --> 26:13.192
Houston says hello.

26:18.300 --> 26:19.578
Hello?

26:28.863 --> 26:31.382
Ask you a question? Sure.

26:32.729 --> 26:34.593
Be nice to have
some interaction.
Shoot.

26:39.114 --> 26:40.529
I seem different to you?

26:42.531 --> 26:43.671
Well, you look
like shit,

26:43.705 --> 26:45.224
but that's becoming
more and more regular.

26:47.226 --> 26:48.227
Why?

26:53.266 --> 26:54.509
Something happened.

26:56.511 --> 26:58.306
I don't know what
that means, Jesse.

26:59.514 --> 27:01.654
Either do I.

27:01.689 --> 27:04.415
Okay you're, like,
boring the shit
out of me right now,

27:04.450 --> 27:06.279
so let's talk
about my stuff.

27:09.075 --> 27:10.111
I spoke to Dany.

27:11.733 --> 27:13.908
No, Tulip. Just hear me out...

27:13.942 --> 27:16.876
I've been hearing you out.
Now you need to hear me out.

27:16.911 --> 27:19.327
I'm done with that life.
I don't want it,
I don't miss it.

27:19.361 --> 27:20.673
Well, that's just
a flat-out lie.

27:20.708 --> 27:21.674
I don't want it.

27:23.331 --> 27:25.954
Why don't you understand?
I'm trying to do
something here.

27:25.989 --> 27:27.438
No, I don't understand.

27:28.301 --> 27:29.371
Course not.

27:29.406 --> 27:32.236
What are you
trying to do, Jesse?
Huh?

27:32.271 --> 27:34.514
Haircut and that
stupid costume?

27:34.549 --> 27:36.102
Remind me
what the hell this is for.

27:36.137 --> 27:37.448
I made a promise.

27:38.139 --> 27:39.243
[SCOFFS]

27:39.278 --> 27:42.661
Right. Be one of
the good guys.

27:43.351 --> 27:44.732
[CHUCKLES]

27:44.766 --> 27:46.665
Course, it's
a joke to you.

27:47.079 --> 27:48.839
But not to me.

27:48.874 --> 27:49.978
If I don't
keep my promise,

27:50.013 --> 27:52.118
if I don't do
everything I can
to save this town,

27:53.430 --> 27:55.674
I'll have to answer to it. Says who?

27:55.708 --> 27:57.606
Says God. God?

27:57.641 --> 28:00.092
The all-time home run King
of promise-breakers?

28:00.126 --> 28:01.334
Now that is a joke.

28:01.369 --> 28:03.578
You don't know
what you're talking about.

28:03.612 --> 28:07.547
Right, 'cause I'm
too stupid to understand
your deep thinking.

28:07.582 --> 28:08.963
Tired of this!

28:10.136 --> 28:12.000
Go back to
your life of crime.

28:13.174 --> 28:15.590
This isn't crime,
Preacher.

28:16.625 --> 28:17.937
This is justice.

28:21.009 --> 28:22.321
Carlos.

28:25.738 --> 28:27.291
[ALARM BELL RINGING]

28:27.326 --> 28:28.327
[TIRES SCREECHING]

28:33.504 --> 28:34.954
Wait!

28:34.989 --> 28:36.162
[TIRES SCREECH]

28:36.197 --> 28:37.336
[TULIP SCREAMS]

28:39.994 --> 28:41.823
Rat-bastard,
money-stealing,

28:41.858 --> 28:44.136
child-killing,
life-ruining
son of a bitch.

28:58.806 --> 29:00.117
You found him.

29:01.187 --> 29:02.533
Last known address.

29:05.536 --> 29:07.746
That promise you made

29:07.780 --> 29:11.335
was a little boy's promise,
made a long time ago.

29:12.612 --> 29:14.511
There's no such thing
as good guys, Jesse.

29:14.545 --> 29:16.237
There's just guys.

29:16.271 --> 29:18.480
Maybe this ain't
how you pictured it

29:18.515 --> 29:21.000
but your daddy's
dead and this
town's past saving.

29:23.796 --> 29:28.249
Jesse, come on.
Let's go kill Carlos.

29:35.152 --> 29:36.395
[TIRES SCREECHING]

29:51.410 --> 29:52.411
[BAG UNZIPPING]

30:10.187 --> 30:12.672
DEBLANC: First the can,
then the Preacher.

30:19.507 --> 30:20.508
[LAUGHS]

30:20.957 --> 30:22.234
[COUGHING]

30:23.476 --> 30:25.858
Nice try, boys.
Nice try.

30:25.893 --> 30:28.274
I don't know how
you keep finding me,
but next time you do,

30:28.309 --> 30:31.036
you need to drive
a different truck,
you pair of idiots!

30:31.070 --> 30:32.037
[CLEARS THROAT]

30:36.455 --> 30:38.457
Now, hang on.
I killed you.

30:38.491 --> 30:40.045
How did you do that?

30:42.495 --> 30:43.496
[CHUCKLES]

30:43.980 --> 30:45.222
Clones.

30:45.844 --> 30:46.845
All right.

30:49.123 --> 30:50.124
Shite.

30:52.126 --> 30:55.646
[SIGHS] Now, we've got
to clean 'em up
all over again. Bollocks!

30:55.681 --> 30:57.027
[MUMBLES INDISTINCTLY]

31:10.765 --> 31:11.835
Oh...

31:11.870 --> 31:13.285
It's gonna take forever.

31:16.529 --> 31:18.048
[DOOR OPENS]

31:18.911 --> 31:20.499
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

31:30.681 --> 31:31.682
All right.

31:33.477 --> 31:35.963
I have a weapon!

31:35.997 --> 31:38.827
You just better
announce yourself!
Let's just be done with it!

31:40.105 --> 31:41.071
[THUDDING]

31:57.881 --> 31:59.227
Don't hurt me.

31:59.262 --> 32:01.126
How do you keep finding me?[FIORE GROANING]

32:01.160 --> 32:02.644
We're not here for you.

32:02.679 --> 32:03.680
[FIORE GROANING]

32:05.647 --> 32:06.752
What?

32:06.786 --> 32:08.236
We're here
for the Preacher.

32:09.617 --> 32:11.239
He has
something of ours.

32:11.274 --> 32:13.793
And we need
to put it back.

32:15.623 --> 32:16.624
[GROANING CONTINUES]

32:26.185 --> 32:28.601
I think, first thing,

32:28.636 --> 32:32.364
is we take a hammer
and we break every
bone in his body.

32:32.398 --> 32:35.815
And I mean, seriously,
like, every single one.

32:39.060 --> 32:41.407
Then maybe something
with battery acid.

32:43.582 --> 32:45.239
Fritos, right?
Chili cheese?

32:45.998 --> 32:46.965
Hey.

32:52.453 --> 32:55.180
Before we go,

32:55.214 --> 32:57.009
there's something
you need to know. [CAR HONKS]

32:57.044 --> 32:59.253
Yeah. Go around. There's something
I got to tell you.

32:59.287 --> 33:00.702
Asshole.

33:00.737 --> 33:02.187
[CAR HONKING]

33:02.221 --> 33:04.637
You deaf? We're talking here! Tulip.

33:04.672 --> 33:06.950
[HONKING CONTINUES] MAN: What the hell
are you doing?

33:06.985 --> 33:08.331
Come on, then, asshole!

33:08.365 --> 33:09.435
MAN: Move out of the way.

33:09.470 --> 33:11.265
TULIP: Let's step to it! Are you serious?

33:11.299 --> 33:12.714
TULIP: Yes, I'm serious!

33:12.749 --> 33:14.716
Come on out of that
piece-of-shit hatchback!

33:14.751 --> 33:15.752
MAN: You're crazy.

33:17.340 --> 33:19.618
TULIP: Yeah,
that's what I thought.

33:20.205 --> 33:21.689
[CAR HONKS]

33:25.141 --> 33:27.212
Anyway. Need to know what?

33:33.321 --> 33:34.736
I need to take a leak.

33:37.325 --> 33:39.017
Fascinating.
Keep me posted.

33:43.849 --> 33:45.851
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

33:55.930 --> 33:57.035
Hey, Preacher.

34:00.624 --> 34:02.040
Hey, Donnie.

34:04.766 --> 34:07.424
Who's the bunny
in the bear trap now?

34:07.459 --> 34:09.737
[BREATHING UNSTEADILY]

34:11.325 --> 34:12.360
Turn around.

34:14.086 --> 34:15.156
Turn around.

34:32.173 --> 34:33.692
Get on your knees.

34:46.187 --> 34:48.120
Now it's your turn
to make the sound.

34:49.846 --> 34:51.192
[LAUGHING]

34:52.987 --> 34:54.678
Whee!

34:54.713 --> 34:56.887
Come on, come on, come on.
Whee! Whee!

35:01.168 --> 35:03.825
Come on, God damn it,
I said squeal!

35:03.860 --> 35:06.104
I ain't gonna squeal
for you, Donnie.

35:06.518 --> 35:08.106
No?

35:08.140 --> 35:09.555
Then you're gonna die for me.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.419
Not that, neither.

35:14.146 --> 35:17.218
But I will make
a deal with you.

35:17.253 --> 35:20.325
Cops find your body,
I'll make it look
like a suicide.

35:22.085 --> 35:25.468
No reason for the whole town
to know I beat you
like a bitch twice.

35:27.573 --> 35:28.574
Stop.

35:30.852 --> 35:31.853
What the hell?

35:32.992 --> 35:33.993
Back up.

35:37.031 --> 35:38.446
Sit down.

35:38.481 --> 35:39.896
[BREATH TREMBLING]

35:44.832 --> 35:46.385
Put the gun in your mouth.

35:53.012 --> 35:54.600
Pull back the hammer.

36:00.227 --> 36:01.193
[WHIMPERS]

36:07.268 --> 36:08.235
[WHIMPERS]

36:16.519 --> 36:17.485
Drop the gun.

36:19.246 --> 36:21.558
[BREATH TREMBLES AND GASPS]

36:24.423 --> 36:25.390
[WHIMPERING]

36:32.673 --> 36:33.881
I get it.

36:39.266 --> 36:40.370
You can go.

36:49.276 --> 36:50.449
Hey, Donnie.

36:50.484 --> 36:51.450
[CAR ALARM BEEPS]

36:56.835 --> 36:57.836
[ENGINE STARTS]

37:00.632 --> 37:03.082
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

37:07.155 --> 37:10.331
What in the whole
wide world were you boys
up to in there?

37:10.366 --> 37:11.643
Changing my mind.

37:16.889 --> 37:17.925
Right.

37:20.030 --> 37:21.860
And so Carlos?

37:21.894 --> 37:24.449
What? We just let him
get away with it?

37:24.483 --> 37:26.416
We... Don't say it!

37:30.351 --> 37:31.456
We leave him to God.

37:34.252 --> 37:35.494
I'm staying.

37:36.668 --> 37:38.117
And I ain't leaving
without you!

37:39.395 --> 37:40.568
Suit yourself.

37:55.169 --> 37:56.929
[HOWLING IN THE DISTANCE]

37:58.552 --> 38:02.107
If our mission
is unsuccessful,
more dead will follow.

38:02.141 --> 38:05.248
If we fail, there will be
no turning back.

38:05.283 --> 38:07.630
So you're not
vampire-killing
vigilantes?

38:07.664 --> 38:10.736
Va... Vampire?
No, no. Not at all.

38:10.771 --> 38:13.394
We don't even know
what that means.

38:13.429 --> 38:15.500
We just want
what's inside the Preacher.

38:15.534 --> 38:16.708
No, I'm sure you do.

38:16.742 --> 38:18.019
[CHUCKLES]

38:18.054 --> 38:19.780
A power like that,
who wouldn't want it?

38:19.814 --> 38:21.333
The question is,
what do you want it for?

38:22.403 --> 38:25.130
Military? Economics?

38:26.683 --> 38:29.445
Mass-scale psycho-sexual
mind control...

38:29.479 --> 38:30.756
What are you
gonna do with it?

38:30.791 --> 38:35.002
Nothing. Not to be
used at all, ever.

38:35.036 --> 38:37.211
That's why it was
put in here
in the first place.

38:39.800 --> 38:41.077
Who are you guys?

38:43.251 --> 38:44.529
We're from
the government.

38:44.563 --> 38:46.254
I figured as much,
with the whole
cloning thing.

38:46.289 --> 38:47.325
I mean, which branch?

38:47.980 --> 38:50.189
FBI, CIA, NSA?

38:50.224 --> 38:51.984
We're from Heaven.

38:54.987 --> 38:56.989
I see. Right.

39:02.443 --> 39:05.619
Honestly, you fellows
think I'm a handful?

39:05.653 --> 39:07.414
Jesse is a bloody
wrecking crew.

39:07.448 --> 39:09.795
You keep coming at him with
coffee cans and chainsaws,

39:09.830 --> 39:11.141
you're gonna wish
you were never born.

39:11.176 --> 39:12.453
It's no good.

39:12.488 --> 39:15.249
From here on out,
let me be your middleman.

39:15.283 --> 39:17.355
I'm just gonna impress
upon him the importance
of your mission,

39:17.389 --> 39:19.564
then I just bring him
to you here.

39:19.598 --> 39:21.980
You're sure the Preacher
will listen to you?

39:22.014 --> 39:23.602
Of course he will,
he's me best mate.

39:29.988 --> 39:32.231
INTERVIEWER: [ON TV]
Does it always kill them?
In the chair?

39:32.266 --> 39:34.510
MAN: Well, I've never
heard of it failing.

39:34.544 --> 39:37.547
INTERVIEWER:
But in the chair,
does it hurt them?

39:37.582 --> 39:38.997
MAN: Not if it's
done properly...

39:39.480 --> 39:41.068
How was your day?

39:45.900 --> 39:47.108
A lot going on.

39:47.143 --> 39:48.144
[SLURPS]

39:50.629 --> 39:53.391
Did you ah, did you hear
about the whole
Tracy Loach thing?

39:56.117 --> 39:57.533
She opened up her eyes.

39:57.567 --> 40:00.121
Preacher came over
and prayed for her

40:00.156 --> 40:01.433
and next thing you
know she just...

40:02.020 --> 40:03.262
Opens them up.

40:06.921 --> 40:08.475
I was thinking
it might be good for her

40:08.509 --> 40:10.442
to maybe have some,
some visitors.

40:10.477 --> 40:12.444
You stay away from her.

40:12.479 --> 40:14.688
You stay away from
the whole family.

40:14.722 --> 40:15.827
Wanna get yourself killed?

40:16.862 --> 40:17.863
No, sir.

40:18.381 --> 40:20.383
Then smarten up.

40:20.418 --> 40:23.559
Prancing around
like everything's polka
dots and moonbeams.

40:25.664 --> 40:27.735
It is a monster swamp.

40:29.150 --> 40:31.877
Murders, mayhem.
Escaped lunatics.

40:33.154 --> 40:34.397
Yes, sir.

40:35.053 --> 40:36.710
Gol darn monster swamp.

40:45.684 --> 40:47.479
First Letter
to the Corinthians.

40:49.274 --> 40:52.726
Chapter 15, verse 51.

40:57.213 --> 41:00.596
"Listen,
I tell you a mystery.

41:00.630 --> 41:02.460
♪ Open up the doors of heaven

41:02.494 --> 41:03.944
"We will not all sleep,

41:05.221 --> 41:06.464
"but we will
all be changed...

41:06.498 --> 41:09.121
♪ I think I'm finally
tired of livin'... ♪

41:09.156 --> 41:10.157
"...In a flash,

41:11.434 --> 41:15.783
"in the twinkling of an eye,
at the last trumpet.

41:15.818 --> 41:18.199
"For the trumpet will sound,

41:18.234 --> 41:21.133
"the dead will be
raised imperishable

41:21.168 --> 41:22.549
"and we will be changed."

41:24.309 --> 41:26.449
[LOW RUMBLING]

41:27.450 --> 41:30.073
[LIQUID BUBBLING]
